Police in Storms River are investigating a culpable homicide case following the death of a woman who was knocked down by a bakkie. The incident occurred at about 3pm on Saturday, close to Woodlands. The pedestrian [aged 39] died on the scene, Captain Gerda Swart said. The bakkie driver was not under the influence of alcohol, she said. There was, however, a lot of smoke on the road from the fires that raged along the Garden Route. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share